sentences: Marilyn Maye McLaughlin (born April 10, 1928) is an American jazz singer, cabaret singer, and musical theater actress.
She recorded for RCA Victor during the 1960s, after which she has had a successful career as a cabaret singer.
In 1942, after her parents divorced, she moved with her mother to Des Moines, Iowa.
At 78, her career was revived in 2006 when she performed at Lincoln Center for the Mabel Mercer Foundation.
In 2008, she received a Distinguished Arts Award from the governor of Kansas.
On October 14, 2012, she received the Lifetime Achievement Award from the Chicago Cabaret Professionals Association.
On September 18, 2012, the Native Sons and Daughters of Greater Kansas City honored Maye with the organization's Outstanding Kansas Citian Award.
After graduating from high school, she moved to Chicago, Illinois, where she drew the attention of Steve Allen, performing first on The Steve Allen Show and then The Tonight Show with Johnny Carson.
She appeared on The Tonight Show 76 times and received a 1966 nomination for the Grammy Award for Best New Artist.
After singing on a commercial for Lincoln Mercury, she was given a new car every year for four years.
She sang in nightclubs and in musicals such as  Can-Can, Mame, and Hello, Dolly.
Her version of "Too Late Now" was included in the Smithsonian Institution recordings of the 20th Century.
